"{\"uid\": \"straitstimes.com-sport-st-picks-champions-of-the-world-10-athletes-to-watch-at-paris-olympics\", \"text\": \"Choose edition  Search  singapore  asia  world  opinion  life  business  sport  Visual  Podcasts  SPH Rewards  STClassifieds  Paid press releases  Advertise with us  FAQs  Contact us  Sign up now:Get the biggest sports news in your inbox  From legends to rising stars, meet 10 top athletes who will take centre stage at the 2024 Paris Olympics.  ST ILLUSTRATIONS: CEL GULAPA  PublishedJul 29, 2024, 01:00 PM  UpdatedJul 29, 2024, 02:12 PM  The Paris 2024 Games will have over 10,000 athletes from 205 nations and territories doing battle till Aug 11 in a bid to bring home Olympic glory.  From legends to rising stars, meet 10 top athletes who will take centre stage in the French capital.  ST ILLUSTRATION: CEL GULAPA  Achievements:Two-time world champion (2017, 2022)  Games participation:2  Olympic medals:1 gold, 1 bronze  ST ILLUSTRATION: CEL GULAPA  Achievements:Her seven Olympic medals tie with Shannon Miller for the most Olympic medals won by an American gymnast. With 30 medals (23 gold, four silver, three bronze), Biles is the most decorated gymnast in World Championships history.  Games participation:3  Olympic medals:4 golds, 1 silver, 2 bronzes  ST ILLUSTRATION: CEL GULAPA  Achievements:At Tokyo 2020, she became Britain's youngest-ever Olympic medallist and the youngest athlete in the Games in 80 years.  Games participation:2  Olympic medals:1 bronze  ST ILLUSTRATION: CEL GULAPA  Achievements:In 2021, she became the first player to score in five consecutive Olympic Games.  Games participation:6  Olympic medals:2 silvers  ST ILLUSTRATION: CEL GULAPA  Personal bests:2hr 1min 9 sec, Berlin Marathon (2022)  Games participation:5  Olympic medals:2 golds, 1 silver, 1 bronze  ST ILLUSTRATION: CEL GULAPA  Achievements:Holds the world records in both the 800m and 1,500m freestyles, and has 21 world titles.  Games participation:4  Olympic medals:7 golds, 3 silvers  ST ILLUSTRATION: CEL GULAPA  Personal bests:100m - 9.81 seconds (2024), 200m - 19.31 seconds (2022)  Games participation:2  Olympic medals:1 bronze  ST ILLUSTRATION: CEL GULAPA  Achievements:Holds the record for the longest reign at world No. 1 and has 14 team and individual world titles.  Games participation:4  Olympic medals:5 golds  ST ILLUSTRATION: CEL GULAPA  Achievements:He has a record 14 French Open titles - the most won by any player at a Grand Slam - earning him the nickname \\\"The King of Clay\\\".  Games participation:4  Olympic medals:2 golds  ST ILLUSTRATION: CEL GULAPA  Achievements:2024 NBA Rookie of the Year  Games participation:1  Sources:OLYMPICS.COM, ESPN, REUTERS, NBC, WORLD ATHLETICS, FIFA, BADMINTON WORLD FEDERATION  Olympics 2024  Olympics  United States  Britain  France  E-paper  Newsletters  Podcasts  RSS Feed  About Us  Terms & Conditions  Personal Data Protection Notice  Need help? Reach us here.  Advertise with us    \"}"